The paper deals with the problem of non-adaptive group testing with inhibitors, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and involves designing efficient algorithms for identifying defective items and inhibitors in a set of items, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the decoding complexity and measurement matrices, which are topics in statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
